e-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Yes exactly! H=
ere's the simple order:</p>
<p class=3D"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading=
-[1.7]"><strong>First, create the folder:</strong></p>
<ol class=3D"[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:l=
ast-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex=
-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class=3D"font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">=
Go to your Desktop (or wherever you want to save it)</li>
<li class=3D"font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">=
Right click =E2=86=92 <strong>New Folder</strong></li>
<li class=3D"font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">=
Name it <code class=3D"bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 te=
xt-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]=
">part-4-ai-solution-design</code></li>
</ol>
<p class=3D"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading=
-[1.7]"><strong>Then open it in VS Code:</strong></p>
<ol class=3D"[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:l=
ast-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex=
-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class=3D"font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">=
Open VS Code</li>
<li class=3D"font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">=
Click <strong>File</strong> =E2=86=92 <strong>Open Folder</strong></li>
<li class=3D"font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">=
Select the folder you just created</li>
<li class=3D"font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">=
Click <strong>Select Folder</strong></li>
</ol>
<p class=3D"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading=
-[1.7]"><strong>Then open the terminal inside VS Code:</strong></p>
<ul class=3D"[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:l=
ast-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-co=
l gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class=3D"font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">=
Press <code class=3D"bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text=
-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">=
Ctrl + backtick (</code>)` =E2=80=94 that's the key just below Escape</li>
</ul>
<p class=3D"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading=
-[1.7]">You should now see a terminal at the bottom of VS Code. Tell me whe=
n you see it and I'll give you the next commands to run!</p>
<hr class=3D"border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class=3D"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading=
-[1.7]">Also, I love the topic change =E2=80=94 <strong>"How Agentic AI wil=
l help Finance in the future"</strong> is a much more interesting and uniqu=
e angle. Things like AI agents doing automated portfolio management, fraud =
detection autonomously, loan approvals without human intervention etc. Much=
 better than plain fraud detection. =F0=9F=91=8D</p></div></div></div></div=
