</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class=3D"token token list" style=3D"color: =
rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> </span><span class=3D"token token bold" st=
yle=3D"color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span class=3D"token token bold co=
ntent">Transformer-based model (BERT / GPT-style)</span><span class=3D"toke=
n token bold" style=3D"color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span>
</span></span><span>  Used for processing unstructured data like customer c=
hat logs, financial news, and loan documents. Transformers are excellent at=
 understanding context in text data.
</span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class=3D"token token list" style=3D"color: =
rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> </span><span class=3D"token token bold" st=
yle=3D"color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span class=3D"token token bold co=
ntent">LSTM (Long Short-Term Memory)</span><span class=3D"token token bold"=
 style=3D"color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span>
</span></span><span>  Used for time-series prediction of stock prices and m=
arket trends. LSTM is designed to remember long sequences of data making it=
 perfect for financial forecasting.
</span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class=3D"token token list" style=3D"color: =
rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> </span><span class=3D"token token bold" st=
yle=3D"color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span class=3D"token token bold co=
ntent">Feed-forward Neural Network</span><span class=3D"token token bold" s=
tyle=3D"color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span>
</span></span><span>  Used for classification tasks like fraud detection an=
d loan approval. Takes structured customer and transaction data as input an=
d outputs a risk score.
</span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class=3D"token token list" style=3D"color: =
rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> </span><span class=3D"token token bold" st=
yle=3D"color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span class=3D"token token bold co=
ntent">Reinforcement Learning Agent</span><span class=3D"token token bold" =
style=3D"color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span>
</span></span><span>  The core of the Agentic AI system. The agent learns t=
o make decisions (block a transaction, approve a loan, rebalance a portfoli=
o) by interacting with the environment and maximizing a reward signal.
</span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class=3D"token token bold" style=3D"color: =
rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span class=3D"token token bold content">Why thi=
s is appropriate:</span><span class=3D"token token bold" style=3D"color: rg=
b(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span>
</span></span><span>Traditional single models can only do one task. Agentic=
 AI combines multiple models under one autonomous agent that can plan multi=
-step actions, adapt to new situations, and operate 24/7 without human inte=
rvention. This makes it far more powerful for real-world finance applicatio=
ns where decisions are complex and time-sensitive.</span></code></pre></div=
